On Percival theres a Eldritch with over 1 million rps. That guy is going to own.<P>Some cool things here, overall I don't like it. Seems like everybody can get some mez/root/etc duration cut spell, resist boost, DISPEL. Wheres the part about caster immunity to meele for a short duration?<P><B>Mastery of Concentration</B> - Reduction to chance of casting interruption. Sad that we have to invest in a skill to get away from a bug.<P><B>Minion Control</B> - Reduced experience taken by pets. &lt;-- LOL, in order for your pets not to rape your exp you have to go out and RvR first so you can buy this skill.<P><B>Volley and Longshot</B> - Oh look, archers finally get their styles.<P><B>Concentration</B> - Resets quickcast timer to allow for a second quickcast. Elderitch&gt;*<P><B>Wild Arcana</B> - A percent to critical for up to double effect with duration-based magic. Does this mean I can AE mez for like 2 minutes now?<P><B>Corporeal Disintegration</B> - AE Dot, Bullseye goes wild! Poor Cabalists, now we can have their class defining skill.<P>Anyway that list is a bitch to look at, I cut it down to Sorcerer only skills. Easier to look at. <A HREF="http://home.earthlink.net/~g2gk/Sorcerer.html" TARGET=_blank>http://home.earthlink.net/~g2gk/Sorcerer.html</A><P>--------------------<P>Garen, Mind Sorcerer :[<BR>Albion, Percival
