<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I know they hate Crowd Control, but.....dang.  They sure swung the bat at it this time, didn't they?  Every class that has the ability to get the purge WILL get it to some degree.  It will be an almost mandatory thing.  <P>I don't think it's so radical that the un-charm Mentalist thing screws with our "last wanted ability"....it just takes away another shield of ours.  And I think it is most harmful to us than other pet classes:  the Cabalist will just resummon, the Theurgist will just resummon, and the Minstrel will just wait until his charm song repulses.  We'll either just lose the pet that we went to great lengths to find and acquire (as the cost for our charm being indefinate, or until we die then they just walk calmly off back home), or we take time out during the battle to recharm it.<P>And finally, our AE DoT.....personally, it is simply dumb as a class-specific ability.  Yes, I say it is a Cabalist-defining ability because they are the only ones in Albion that have it.  Sorcerers *can* use DoTs, but generally don't.  Shouldn't a class-specific ability somewhat reflect the unique qualities of the class?  Oh, wait, I forgot, Mythic considers us a square peg being shoved into round holes.  We don't have a "vision" of what we're meant to be, we don't have a "place".  Are we the Crowd Control of Albion?  Maybe.  But Mythic didn't give us a CC ability, so I guess not.  Are we the main Pet class of Albion?  Probably not, because we didn't even get the minus-pet-experience ability, let alone a class-specific one.  <P>No, we get an AE DoT.  It isn't very impressive, it isn't very unique, and it's my opinion that it doesn't represent "The Sorcerer" at all.  Just a cheap way for us to get RPs since our most common weapon, Mez, doesn't get us any.
</FONT>
